   <h1>The Troll&#39;s Bane Chronicle</h1>

   <h2>The fifth year of the new era: September</h2>

<p>In the Year 5, on the 1st of september annouces Emily Xahep that she leaves for a while, because she's not sure of her sanity.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 3rd of september annouces Alysha that Caden Fayed, son of Caitlin Fergus and Pendar Fayed was born on the 20th of Malas and that Moathia was the midwife.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 6th of september annouces Pendar Fayed, captain of the town guard, that Aokan Folkbjorn is a wanted man for bringing Dravish back to live and being a fellower of Drakhen.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 6th of september annouces Marius Eisenhauer that he withdraws from his work as forester of Trolls Bane. Slasthulphus offers his help but it comes to no decision.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 7th of september annouces the leadership of Varshikar that Trolls Bane is in debt of several things a long debate follows. </p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 9th of september annouces Emily Xahep that all citizen of Gobaith should watch out for William Elderberry for he seems a little insane.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 9th of september publishes Mairead some drawings of different people. Later the pictures seemed to be taken off, only one remained.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 9th of september announces Culandria that her and Stephen Rothman's son, Skyler Rothman was born on the 16th Findos.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 10th of september looks Markous of the White Flame for a farmer to work in the gardens of the Eldan Monastery. Later he announces that Peeny Peelburrow is the new farmer.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 12th of september announces Rasthor that he is leaving that island because the citizen are too violant and disturbing for him.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 13th of september asks Capus to not cut down the cherry trees in town for he planted them and they are too rare to loose them.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 13th of september annouces Thalados Artemetus that a ceremony will held in Vanima to remember Arynne Halfmoon, Tyveria and Rahne Devereaux.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 16th of september asks Capus for help to rerive an unknown stranger who fell in a fight against beholders.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 17th of september looks Shandariel el Lysanthrai for the parents of a girl named Kalie, no one seemed to answer.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 17th of september looks Friedwulfa for a good carpenter who can sell her handles for all kind of tools.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 18th of september announces Farel Leonsepth that the man called Aokan is held in jail.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 18th of september places Mebririth a bounty of thousand coins on the head of an orc who injured him inside of town. It comes to a long debate because Mebririth himself is a known criminal.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 19th of september informs Linella Finn indignant that she doesn't like it that people plant fir trees in the shop and that at least the elves should watch over it.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 19th of september warns Slasthulphus that the wild is coming over Trolls Bane again since fir trees are growing inside the shop. He also states that it is not his fault this time and that he leave the town until it is cleared out.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 19th of september announces Pendar Fayed that Markous has the right to hand a day long ban due to the recent orc attacks.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 19th of september asks Markous for help to rebuild the Eldan Monastery and also for donations.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 20th of september looks Mairead for someone called Maphitus. No one seemed to see him.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 20th of september calles Pendar Fayed all men to the armes due to the threat of an orc attack. Many seem to be willing to attend.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 20th of september askes Xantor all dwarves and friends of Silverbrand to help him to explore the tunnels under the graveyard. Many seemed to be interested. Later he informs that it was very interesting but that next to mummys, skelletons and beholders nothing special can be found.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 22nd of september asks Djironnyma all mages of the island for a meeting to discuss the matter why the magic doesn't flow. </p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 23rd of september warns Linella Finn that there is a thief in town who works with filthy tricks.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 23rd of september appears a faked note saying that the lich Dravish was captured. It is signed with the names of Pendar Fayed, Culandria and Callith.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 24th of september announces Callith that Capus is banned from town. Bailey Thunningan adds later that she jailed him.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 24th of september announces Markous that the orcs Alkuurg und Ko are banned from the town of Trolls Bane for attacking people in town.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 25th of september reminds Pendar Fayed everyone that the White Flames supports Trolls Bane and that the townguard helps everyone who needs it.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 24th of september asls Brother Selisidour why the leadership of Varshikar placed a bounty on his head. Later it becomes clear that it was all faked.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 26th of september accuses Gulkurg Ironbrow a member of the White Flames to attack him inside of town. Markous kindly asks him for the name but gets no respond.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 27th of september announces Calimal that she and Tiklian are awaiting a child.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 27th of september offers Ko his service as mercenary.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 28th of september annouces Callith, captain of the town guard, that the White Flame does not have any special powers Pendar granted them. but that they may continue guard Pendar.</p>
<p>In the Year 5, on the 28th of september asks Ko whether the people wants him to be banned or free. Most seem to want him banned.</p> 

